-- Microsoft Xbox Sales Get 49% of U.S. Market Last Month
-- B y   C l i f f   E d w a r d s
-- 2012-10-11T22:52:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-11/microsoft-xbox-sales-get-49-of-u-s-market-last-month.html
Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  said U.S. retailers
sold 270,000 Xbox video-game consoles last month, citing data
from market researcher NPD Group Inc.  The sales represented 49 percent of the market for current
generation consoles, Redmond, Washington-based Microsoft said
today in an e-mailed statement. Stores sold 438,000 Xbox players
in the same month a year ago, according to NPD data at the time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
